HEADWORD: Ranula
<hw>Ran"u*la</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧n"⟦usl⟧*l⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., a little frog, a little swelling on the tongue of cattle, dim.
of <ets>rana</ets> a frog.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A cyst formed
under the tongue by obstruction of the duct of the submaxillary
gland.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ranunculaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
